targets.query:
from(bucket: v.defaultBucket)
  |> range(start: v.timeRangeStart, stop: v.timeRangeStop)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_measurement"] =~ /\b${devices:regex}\b/)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_field"] =~ /\b${parameters:regex}\b/)
  |> aggregateWindow(every: v.windowPeriod, fn: mean)
  |> yield(name: "mean")

panels.description:
If you need to add GNSS position and 3D inertial sensor data to the OBD2 data from your car, we recommend to use the CANmod.gps as an add-on for your CANedge.

You can then log CAN/OBD2 data via channel 1 from your car - and record timesynced GNSS/IMU data via channel 2 from the CANmod.gps module. 

The combined data can be processed and visualized in e.g. Grafana dashboards as seen here.

targets.query:
from(bucket: v.defaultBucket)
  |> range(start: v.timeRangeStart, stop: v.timeRangeStop)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_measurement"] =~ /\b${devices:regex}\b/)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_field"] == "Latitude" or r["_field"] == "Longitude")
  |> aggregateWindow(every: v.windowPeriod, fn: median)
  |> yield(name: "median")
